<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Panama City,Florida 10/19/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.89)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12683'>Richard "Omegasyn28" Spedale</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12683&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> October 20, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont">    Greetings from the Retirement capital of the world.If it is ancient and driving very slowly(in a Cadillac) is is here.Not much here on the off season(P.C.Spring break rocks)<br>
so I am supposed to have time to play.Negative ghost rider.<br>
Between work and school I find myself spending less time at the shop and more time stressed out studying or working.But no matter what I FIND time to play LOTR every other week.We&#39;ve experienced a lag in attendance (Only about 6 or 8 players a Tourney)but even if theres only me and Paul I will continue to play(I really enjoy Playing).This tourney was one of my fav&#39;s not because I won (I didn&#39;t)but because we had a good group of players from Tallahasse show up.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind this will be a long report.I love detailing the game(It helps me remember my mistakes and helps the players see thiers.)<br>
<br>
Tourney details<br>
<br>
Att-9 players<br>
2 Moria decks<br>
4 Ringwraith decks<br>
1 Urik deck(me)<br>
1 Red eye deck<br>
1 &quot;jank&quot;deck(mixture)<br>
<br>
Round one Richard vs.Carlos<br>
Moria vs.Isengard<br>
Great a Moria deck.I just love how they swarm my tiny fellowship (4 people)at site five.Carlos is getting tougher and tougher to beat.I find myself relieved to know his fellowship is weaker than his minion side so I can at least win on one front.(when he fixes it I&#39;m in trouble)<br>
Anyway I bid Zero and he bids not zero,and he goes first.Crap no pony.Oh wait he put in the pony, cool.<br>
He throws down a mass of Hobbits and smiles thinking he&#39;s got me on denial.I state to him that hobbits cant win the game alone against uriks(everybody knows that)he then smiles again and plays Gandalf and Aragorn at neg 2.(I hate pippin).The game proceeds uneventfully (Stealths on both sides)until the bridge.I hold my breath as i look at my naked companions and step onto the brige waiting for the end to come.Well there&#39;s a runner and another and an....nope no other minions yessssss! he drops the Balrog (I love Hobbit stealth) and I  double to dimral dale(yes I have a pair of kahunas, thier quite large thank you.)<br>
Again i wait for the horde.Nope he say&#39;s I pass.Wow thats a first.After that I pretty much cleaned up staying ahead while punching his fellowships clock as they desperatly tried to follow me.(Carlos you need to run A.bow.)At site nine I faced a huge swarm of minions but my now fully equipped and beefy fellowship had no problem butchering more than a few orcs to end the long road.Good game carlos.<br>
<br>
Props-Frying pan.It not only makes a great omelet it also cracks goblin skulls quite efficiently..<br>
Carlos for his good sportsmanship(I would have ripped my deck up if I had the draws he had.)<br>
Slops- Carlos&#39;s draws.I hate winning by luck.<br>
<br>
<br>
Match 2-Richard vs.I dont remember his name.<br>
Red-eye vs Isengard<br>
I liked these guys from Tally.Although they seemed a little overconfident(they probably underestimated us )they were very good sportsman and I hope they show up for the next tourney.We had a pretty good match with me leading most of the way.I cant say that I agreed with his minion choice but he had me concerned a few times(No hates or bowmen or UTWE in deck)just beefy redeyes.However the Pan works on them as well and I had the race down at site nine.Good game man.if you read this D-mail me and I help you with your deck(I think i have some Hates and bowmen I might hook you up with.<br>
 Props-On a fellow F.F,Everquest player.good game man.<br>
Slops -He pulled My only Sleep Carahdras with a Random discard.If he would have had U.T.W.E.I would have been through.<br>
<br>
Match Three Richard vs.Toger Reppen<br>
Urik vs.Ringwraith<br>
Torger is one matchup I always have problems with.His quiet friendly exterior hides a very competitive person who is just as good at the game as I am.<br>
I make this on quick so I don&#39;t dwell on my STUPID mistakes.<br>
I got to play my own sites and I foolishly moved into HIS ford of Bruenon.Good game Torger I sure hope you buried my Frodo in a deep grave so the worms don&#39;t eat him.<br>
<br>
Props- Torgers facial expression never changed as I said I would move to his Ford.(I would have had a WOOD that would have raised the Table)It&#39;s like doubling to Hollin, Just don&#39;t even think it.<br>
Slops-Pauls laughter as I told him what happened(He was Undefeated)<br>
<br>
Match four (final for second Place)<br>
Richard vs.Gabriel.<br>
Urik vs.Ringwraith<br>
This was one of the best Matches I have ever played.I foolishly boast my record of Nazgul kills to be in the hundreds and I only have three losses so far in standard and friendly play to these abominations.I am part of the exclusive club of people who think cards like Defiance and Mysterious wizard are necessities in decks.I just LOVE overwhelming the Balrog.<br>
Anyways I looked forward to this match as Gabriel looked to be a Great player and He boasted that Nazgul are the minions to beat.Hmmmmm.We&#39;ll see.<br>
I bid 0 to his something or other It doesnt matter I dont care who goes first or second. Either I draw a good hand or I lose early.<br>
He choses to go sec...Nope he wants to go first HUH????<br>
Well maybe he doesn&#39;t want me to play the pony NOPE.He runs the pony.Oh well.I still think gabe had never plyed against a good urik deck because when I dropped Saruman and worry and a warrior and a leiutenant and a Troop and a raider,he assumed that the archery phase still existed.He almost exerted Legolas to try t wound the warrior but when he saw me reach for Saruman he quickly reachedfor him and read him<br>
&quot;DARN&quot;he said(well it was a little more colorful than that)but I cant write what hesaid I ll be booted off.<br>
I probably could have won by doubling to nine but It would have been close.(he had a ton of Nazgul in hand I peeked with Glamdring)but i chose to corrupt his ringbearer in a very close game.Good game Gabe.<br>
<br>
Props- to Prince of Mirkwood.Beating Elvis(The King)with his pale blade and a Morgul blade in a skirmish ie. 2 Defiance,2 servants.<br>
Slops-To whomever passed wind during the match(was it me?)It really Stank.<br>
<br>
I got a pack of FOTR and A Pack of ROTE and a few of Torgers beutifully crafted gay rares for second place.I pulled a Rare frodo and nothing else decent.<br>
Thanks to Torgerfor a good Tourney. I hope that we all continue to play this game for a long time coming.<br>
